{{MemoriaLore
| jp = 生け花はまるで鏡のよう。<br />いけながら見つめているのは花ではなく、己の心。<br />見せかけだけの華やかさは、ただ虚ろなだけ。<br />研ぎ澄まし、洗練し、突き詰めた先に美は存在する。
| en = Flower arranging is just like a mirror.<br />While arranging, what you are gazing at are not flowers, but your own heart.<br />If it seems like nothing but showiness, it's just emptiness.<br />But if you delve into the polish and the refinement, then the beauty exists.
| na = Flower arranging is like a mirror. You observe your own heart as you work, rather than the flowers. The beauty you see on the surface is only skin-deep; true beauty is found only beyond the work you refine and hone.
}}

